[[File:Northlight_Film_scanning.jpg|right|thumb| Filmlight's Northlight single frame film scanning unit]]
'''FilmLight''' is a manufacturer of color grading systems, image processing applications and workflow tools for the [[film]] and [[television]] industry.
The company is headquartered in [[London]].

==Products==
FilmLight's first product was the Northlight film scanner,&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.filmlight.ltd.uk/products/northlight/overview_nl.php Northlight film scanner]&lt;/ref&gt; a [[motion picture film scanner]] capable of scanning 16, 35 or 65&amp;nbsp;mm film formats. It is commonly used for feature film effects, [[Digital Intermediate]] and archiving. It then followed with the Baselight&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.filmlight.ltd.uk/products/baselight/overview_bl.php Baselight]&lt;/ref&gt; colour grading system and the Truelight&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.filmlight.ltd.uk/products/truelight/overview_tl.php Truelight]&lt;/ref&gt; colour management system.

